# User UI/UX Preferences

- Prioritize clarity and low cognitive load: clear hierarchy, obvious primary actions.
- Design mobile-first when the app is used on phones; touch targets at least 44px.
- Support dark mode for all main surfaces and text (e.g. Tailwind `dark:` variants).
- Use subtle borders and backgrounds (e.g. opacity like `/0.06`, `/0.08`) and consistent radius (`rounded-xl` / `rounded-2xl`).
- Use transitions on interactive elements (e.g. `transition-all duration-200`).
- Prefer backdrop blur on floating panels; keep a consistent visual language across toolbars and cards.
